  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Bleeding is one of the most important causes of mortality and morbidity in patients.&#xD;
&#xD;
      Hb levels are the most prevalently utilized monitoring parameter in hemorrhagic patients in&#xD;
      the hemodynamic sense. Hemoglobin determination is studied at laboratories along with blood&#xD;
      gasses or complete blood analysis. Recently, non-invasive techniques where measurement is&#xD;
      made from the fingertips have been offered for use. One of these techniques is non-invasive&#xD;
      hemoglobin (SpHb) measurement. SpHb is used as a trend monitor. Based on the severity of&#xD;
      bleeding, the compensatory mechanisms of patients may be disrupted. This situation may lead&#xD;
      to lower levels of toleration of anemia during bleeding. The relationship between blood&#xD;
      transfusion and mortality is under debate.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
